{
  "stem": "1568.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I don't know, none went-- just for some reason I-- I came out at Flossenburg.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, I believe it was around April that Flossenburg was getting to be liquidated, [SIGHS] and that was winter time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It would have been [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] end of-- no, it was April.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was still winter.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was April, I guess there was-- must have been still snow, still winter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They send us-- they put us in wagons, trains.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Trains consisted of open wagons and closed wagons.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I ended up in one of the open wagons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There are probably about 70, 80 people in a wagon.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The nourishments that you would get would be that they would throw a few loaves of bread over the wagon.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't how they put it inside their other ones, but to our wagons they threw it over the wagon.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Again, I sometimes would land a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "How I did, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because again, when you have 70 people trying to get a few pieces of bread-- I know it was snowing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I loved the snow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "At least I wasn't thirsty, I was able to eat snow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the morning, you would wake up and you would find that you're sleeping on corpses.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] What would they do?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They would-- strong people would pick up the corpses and just threw them overboard.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SIGHS] The following day, all of a sudden we heard planes flying over us, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and we heard gunfire, machine fire, and realized that it was American or British planes were shooting up the train.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were able to [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [? shoot ?] like a-- like a mortars so they couldn't move anymore.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
